summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganGive BackL'Oreal's True Match Super-Blendable Foundation is medium coverage and formulated with up to 6 pigments for your most precise match.
details: DetailsBenefitsFormulated with up to 6 pigments for the most precise matchLocks in moisture & provides medium coverage with a natural finish that adapts to any skin color and textureSuper blendable - it's like you can't tell where your foundation ends & your skin beginsAvailable in various skin-like shades to go beyond matching skin tone & match your skin cool, neutral or warm undertoneIncludes a pump99% of women found their true match**In a consumer test of 312 womenFormulated WithoutAlcoholFragranceAnimal-derived ingredientsItem 2602421How To UseShake well before using. reviews.headline: Feels Great
reviews.comments: I was surprised and how wear this wears! The coverage is just want I needed and It does not dry out my skin.

reviews.headline: Great foundation
reviews.comments: This is a great foundation. The price is perfect and the shade range is great. It feels very light on the skin. I love that you can thin it out or build it up for more coverage. The only con is that it shows all texture on the skin. Ive tried different primers and techniques but no matter what all texture is so obvious with this foundation.

reviews.headline: BEAUTIFUL finish
reviews.comments: I had to purchase without shade matching/testing, and grabbed two shades. one for when I'm tan, and one shade lighter for when I'm not. I have no idea how, but they were absolutely perfect matches and looked great on. it wears great, has an insanely beautiful finish, and is a true medium/buildable coverage. I've heard so much about this foundation and usually use a super expensive tinted moisturizer with SPF when I do wear makeup, but had an outside summer wedding to attend and wanted something with more staying power and coverage. this was perfect! compares to high end without the ridiculous price tag.

reviews.headline: DONT BUY IF YOU HAVE PALE SKIN
reviews.comments: im a very pale female ans because of that i got recommended this foundation. at firts i was hopeful since a EMPLOYEE who was also VERY pale recomennded it. as soon as i put it on you could tell sm was up taht it wasnt the same shade as the bottle. however i let it sit. 10 minutes later i look and it looks like a BRUISE it became this rlly ugly like yellow color that looked like when you first get a bruise and its sorta yellow it was so bad. i had to wipe it off and redo my makeup. DONT RECOMMEND.

reviews.headline: great
reviews.comments: one of the best drug store foundations i've used!

reviews.headline: Amazing for the price
reviews.comments: I am a life long consumer of expensive foundation. I've wasted so money on the wrong colors and shades that don't quite work. I'm stunned that C3 is the best and most natural match I've ever had.

reviews.headline: My NEW favorite foundation‚ù§Ô∏è
reviews.comments: Absolutely JUST LOVE this foundation long lasting and just BEAUTIFUL on my skin and has a natural finish look !! Its now my #1 Foundation that i will be repurchasing for now on!! üòç‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.headline: Good foundation
reviews.comments: This is a pale girl favorite! A natural finish from a drugstore foundation is just what I need in a day to day. The shade range is good on the pale side, I haven't had this good of a match with other products. My only gripe with this is it might not last as long as other foundations, but personally I don't mind as it gets the job done for a good price point.

reviews.headline: Amazing Product!
reviews.comments:
This is a true powerhouse of foundations. 
Super affordable, amazing color match, light on the skin, buildable. Stamping into the skin will give you the best airbrushed look. This got rid of my redness after putting on only one layer.

reviews.headline: Shocked
reviews.comments:
this foundation has been out for a while. I decided on a whim to give it a try.

I have dry skin, but I do a lot of skin prep before applying make up, and this is amazing.

I was skeptical cause I normally go for hydrating foundations... but this did really well for me- and at half of the cost of other foundations I have used.

reviews.headline: Not for aging skin
reviews.comments: I purchased this foundation from an article that highly recommended it as one of the top foundations for aging skin. In fact, this is one of the top foundations NOT to wear if you have aging skin. It will showcase and emphasize every line ir crease on your face and it also leaves a very greasy appearance. It's terrible it creases and it makes you look much older.

reviews.headline: Only buy if you have 100% perfect skin
reviews.comments: Foundation is thin, has a weird finish, and shows off anytjing you dknt want shown off like little mustache, acne, or tour pores. It also creases under eyes, smile lines, or eyebrow lines

reviews.headline: Beautiful finish on combination skin
reviews.comments:
Have been using this foundation for the past 2 weeks, has a medium to full coverage depending on how you build it up.
I do recommend you moisturize and prep skin before, without prep can cake around nose and under eye.

reviews.headline: This is my new go to. Will continue to buy!
reviews.comments: I saw some girl recommended this product and I had to try it. Trust me it is even better than I thought. It blends so nice and I get compliments on how good my makeup looks.

reviews.headline: Shade range not accurate
reviews.comments:
I purchased a neutral medium shade but it is so pink I can't use it. The shades are not described in my opinion. 

The formula is nice but nothing amazing.

reviews.headline: OBSESSED
reviews.comments: so good i finally found a foundation that looks amazing and blends so good and color match is amazing would definitely recommend!

reviews.headline: Blends nicely, natural finish
reviews.comments: Blends nicely, natural finish & good coverage. However it can get patchy throughout the day.

reviews.headline: Smooth
reviews.comments: Smooth coverage, velvety finish, good color range, fairly lightweight feeling on the skin all day. My rosacea (at age 25) got irritated by this product. I think it isnt as breathable for my skin as it feels, but would recommend trying for someone els! Very affordable for the quality of product

reviews.headline: pretty dang spot on to my shade!
reviews.comments: I was very surprised by this product. I've always used the infallible line by L'Oreal, but I felt like it was getting too heavy for my liking. This foundation was a pleasant surprise. I did use the "shade finder" tool online, and I picked the right shade first try. it feels comfortable and lightweight with just enough coverage to still feel "natural." it blends nicely with any tool. I haven't tried it without a setting spray yet, but it seems to last for hours, I'll have to test out longevity otherwise.

reviews.headline: Good but oxidation is bad
reviews.comments: Personally this foundation doesnt crease for me and is very buildable but ive noticed it oxidizes ALOT so I dong plan on using it anymore

faceoff_positive.comments:
I love this makeup and buy it 4 at a time to make sure I never run out. Unfortunately, sometimes my complexion is darker due to sun exposure. I am religious about reapplying sunblock in the afternoon, but when I wear foundation it would mess that up, so I want a foundation with sunblock in it that I can reapply instead. Up to W8 that works (my Winter shade). But Spring, Summer and Fall I need W9, and it appears this makeup simply does not carry a shade darker than W8 that has sunblock in it. At least I can't find it anywhere. Why change the formula just because it's a darker shade? Everyone needs to be wearing sunblock! 

But for the Winter, when the one with sunblock matches my complexion, this is a perennial favorite. Looks fresh all day even if I skip reapplying after lunch. I'm only reapplying to refresh the sunscreen application. Very natural looking on one's skin. I tend to apply it with a damp beauty blender and really press it into my skin. You wouldn't know I have makeup on except that no one's skin looks that flawless naturally. Great makeup.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love it with the sunblock

faceoff_negative.comments: The foundation itself is very good.  I have been using it for many years.  But the new style of bottle is the pits!  This new 'squirt' bottle allows the foundation to run down the outside of the bottle wasting the product. It is always a mess and needs to be cleaned up after every use.  Just go back to the old bottle with the screw top. It works and is simple, efficient and I would think cheaper than this mess you have now.
faceoff_negative.headline: Good product, bad bottle.
